</svg></contents>
		</hasCover>
		<dc:abstract rdf:parseType="Resource">
			<contents rdf:parseType="Literal"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en" xml:lang="en">
	<p>A corpus of, roughly speaking, every creative work that I (<a href="https://go.KIBI.family/">KIBI Gô</a>) created prior to graduating college mid‐2016, based on the categorization system I used circa 2013 and updated periodically thereafter.  Back in these days I cared a lot about keeping a record of <em>literally everything</em>, so you will find a lot of inconsequential stuff in this collection.</p>
	<p><i>BJMNS</i> is a generic username that I employed often during this time, replacing the earlier <i>TF</i> which I had used for artistic works in middle and high school.  There is no clear delineation between projects created under the two monikers, so they are unified here.</p>
	<p>In a similar fashion, projects were associated with a variety of “publishing houses”, including <i>Testing Hat</i>, <i>Storytime Magic!</i>, and <i>B@N</i>.  You’ll see marks such as these appearing on many of the (especially early) drafts.</p>
</div></contents>
		</dc:abstract>
		<forAuthor>
	<Author rdf:about="https://go.KIBI.family/About/#me">
		<fullTitle xml:lang="en">BJMNS</fullTitle>
	</Author>
		</forAuthor>
		<hasProjects>
	<rdf:Seq>
		<rdf:_1>
	<Project rdf:about="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::1">
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="./1/"/>
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="#bjmns:1"/>
		<identifier rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#NCName">zl</identifier>
		<fullTitle xml:lang="en">Tally Magiczl</fullTitle>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q8337"/>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/works/2126644"/>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/works/4035856"/>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/works/4995027"/>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/works/12103280"/>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/works/13093944"/>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/subjects/sh2008113556"/>
		<dc:abstract rdf:parseType="Resource">
			<contents rdf:parseType="Literal"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en" xml:lang="en">
	<p><a href="http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q8337"><code>wikidata:Q8337</code></a> was the first book series I got into as a (very young) kid, and when I was very little I used to run around pretending I was a <a href="http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q8337"><code>wikidata:Q8337</code></a> wizard or witch.  But, being an inventive sort, I got bored of this pretty quickly and decided to just create my <em>own</em> magical fantasy boarding‐school, whence <a href="https://go.KIBI.family/Corpora/bjmns.tumblr.com,2013/#bjmns:1" resource="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::1"><code>bjmns:1</code></a>.</p>
	<p>Most of the writing I did in elementary school was set in this universe, which I mostly put to rest after <a href="https://go.KIBI.family/Corpora/bjmns.tumblr.com,2013/#bjmns:1:1:2003-09:1" resource="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::1:1:2003-09:1"><code>bjmns:1:1:2003-09:1</code></a>. Because the actual number of stories is unknown (and many were doubtless lost to time), early versions are organized by year and month of inception.</p>
</div></contents>
		</dc:abstract>
		<includes>
