		</rdf:_2>
		<rdf:_3>
	<Project rdf:about="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::3">
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="./3/"/>
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="#bjmns:3"/>
		<identifier rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#NCName">palm</identifier>
		<fullTitle xml:lang="en">In the Palm of My Hand</fullTitle>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q16938261"/>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q6816260"/>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/hubs/28f3ae7fcfe5d09906fbd8cc80e5781c"/>
		<dc:abstract rdf:parseType="Resource">
			<contents rdf:parseType="Literal"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en" xml:lang="en">
	<p>A story about technology, connectivity, transhumanism, and internet surveillance.  In what I’m now thinking to be the summer after sixth grade, I was sitting in my room and <a href="http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q16938261"><code>wikidata:Q16938261</code></a> came on and that basically inspired this whole concept about smart devices and surveillance and resistance and all of that stuff.</p>
	<p>The history of this project is recorded in more detail in <a href="https://go.KIBI.family/Corpora/bjmns.tumblr.com,2013/8/1/0/3/" resource="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::8:1:0:3"><code>bjmns:8:1:0:3</code></a> if you can get past the highschool writing.  There isn’t any record of <a href="https://go.KIBI.family/Corpora/bjmns.tumblr.com,2013/3/-1/" resource="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::3:-1"><code>bjmns:3:-1</code></a> or <a href="https://go.KIBI.family/Corpora/bjmns.tumblr.com,2013/3/0/" resource="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::3:0"><code>bjmns:3:0</code></a> in the original BJMNS <abbr title="Branching Notational System">BNS</abbr> categorization, so I’ve added them as volumes −1 and 0 here.</p>
</div></contents>
		</dc:abstract>
		<includes>
	<Volume rdf:about="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::3:-1">
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="./3/-1/"/>
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="#bjmns:3:-1"/>
		<identifier rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#NCName">penny</identifier>
		<index rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">-1</index>
		<fullTitle xml:lang="en">Vote for Penny</fullTitle>
		<abbreviatedTitle xml:lang="en">Vote 4 Penny</abbreviatedTitle>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://id.loc.gov/resources/works/4943220"/>
		<dc:abstract rdf:parseType="Resource">
			<contents rdf:parseType="Literal"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en" xml:lang="en">
	<p> In . . . what evidence strongly suggests to be the sixth grade, student body elections happening at school (presumably, at the beginning of the year for sixth graders) inspired me to come up with a story about school elections of my own, featuring a protagonist named Penny, and with pennies‐the‐currency standing in as some symbol or other.  This is the <em>original</em> slice‐of‐life school fic, and inspired all the ones to come in varying degrees.</p>
	<p>(In particular, the character of Penelope Baines from <a href="https://go.KIBI.family/Corpora/bjmns.tumblr.com,2013/41/" resource="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::41"><code>bjmns:41</code></a> is inspired by this Penny.)</p>
	<p>That said, I never actually wrote any of it.  But the protagonist of <a href="https://go.KIBI.family/Corpora/bjmns.tumblr.com,2013/3/1/" resource="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::3:1"><code>bjmns:3:1</code></a> was ostensibly originally created for this story.</p>
</div></contents>
		</dc:abstract>
		
	</Volume>
		</includes>
		<includes>
	<Volume rdf:about="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::3:0">
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="./3/0/"/>
		<owl:sameAs rdf:resource="#bjmns:3:0"/>
		<identifier rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#NCName">santa</identifier>
		<index rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#integer">0</index>
		<fullTitle xml:lang="en">The Santa Affair</fullTitle>
		<abbreviatedTitle xml:lang="en">Santa Affair</abbreviatedTitle>
		<inspiration rdf:resource="http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q97940458"/>
		<dc:abstract rdf:parseType="Resource">
			<contents rdf:parseType="Literal"><div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" lang="en" xml:lang="en">
	<p>Inspired not insignificantly by <a href="http://www.wikidata.org/entity/Q97940458"><code>wikidata:Q97940458</code></a>, tells the story of a boy who uncovers a global Santa conspiracy and I think almost ends Christmas.  The protagonist is the same as in <a href="https://go.KIBI.family/Corpora/bjmns.tumblr.com,2013/3/1/" resource="tag:bjmns.tumblr.com,2013:bns::3:1"><code>bjmns:3:1</code></a>, only as a teen.</p>
</div></contents>
		</dc:abstract>
		<hasNote>
